note.p:
Pub. L. 119–37, div. F, title V, § 6506(b), Nov. 12, 2025, 139 Stat. 645, provided that: “A final administrative order on nonprescription sunscreen active ingredients issued under section 3854 of the Coronavirus Aid, Relief, and Economic Security Act (Public Law 116–136; 21 U.S.C. 360fff–3 note) shall— “(1) account for historical data regarding the safety of sunscreen active ingredients that have previously been accepted for marketing in the United States;
“(2) account for the role of broad spectrum sunscreens with a Sun Protection Factor of 15 or higher in effective skin cancer prevention; and
“(3) incorporate the evidence and testing standards for sunscreen active ingredients detailed in section 505G(r) of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act (21 U.S.C. 355h) (as added by subsection (a)).”
